            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "Chhaava: A Timeless Tribute to Traditional Sarees and Royal Elegance",
            "text": "<p>In a cinematic era often ruled by glitz and fast fashion, the upcoming period drama <a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/de/title/tt27922706/\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><em>Chhaava</em></span></a> stands out for more than just its storyline. The film, based on the legendary life of Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj, the son of Shivaji Maharaj, has drawn attention for its <strong>rich visual storytelling and authentic costume design</strong>, especially the <strong>traditional sarees</strong> that bring 17th-century Maratha royalty to life.</p><h2>Sarees That Speak History</h2><p>Set in a time of valor, politics, and cultural pride, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chhaava\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><em>Chhaava</em></span></a> carefully resurrects the royal aesthetics of the Maratha empire. The costume design team, guided by historical research, leaned heavily into handwoven silks, earthy tones, and rich textures. The women in the film are seen adorned in <a href=\"https://www.indyvogue.com/collections/vendors?filter.p.m.saree.type=Paithani&page=1&q=indyvogue&srsltid=AfmBOorJ31839jZOLdcuddY-1ozGiZTA1sjAx-g9bNl9CTgIM_tDQo9m\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>Paithani sarees</strong></span></a>, a hallmark of Maharashtrian tradition, known for their intricate zari work, vibrant borders, and classic peacock motifs.</p><p>Every pleat, every drape in the film is intentional. The sarees not only enhance the beauty of the characters but also serve as a <strong>visual narrative of status, tradition, and pride</strong>. The muted golds, deep maroons, forest greens, and indigo blues reflect the color palette of the times—regal yet grounded.</p><p><strong>Read More:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.indyvogue.com/blogs/indyvogue-fashion-center/how-to-wear-silk-sarees-in-modern-style-for-this-ganesh-chaturthi\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">How to Wear Silk Sarees in Modern Style for This Ganesh Chaturthi – IndyVogue</span></a> </p>",
            "subhd_color": "#222222",
            "hd_color": "#222222",
            "des_color": "#878787",
