            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2></h2><h2></h2><h2>Empowering Through Authenticity</h2><p>What makes <em>Chhaava</em> especially impactful is its decision to keep the costumes deeply rooted in history, rather than taking creative liberties with fusion fashion. It celebrates the strength, dignity, and beauty of Maratha women, using sarees as their armor of elegance. The characters don <strong>navvari (nine-yard) sarees</strong>, styled traditionally with a waistband (kamarpatta), nath (nose ring), and moon-shaped bindis—reminiscent of paintings and portraits from the era.</p><p>The film does not just dress its characters; it <strong>resurrects a whole culture</strong> through clothing.</p>",
            "subhd_color": "#222222",
            "hd_color": "#222222",
            "des_color": "#878787",
            "use_shadow": false,
