            "text_size": "40,15",
            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>Reviving Heritage on the Big Screen</h2><p>Costume-led storytelling in <em>Chhaava</em> is likely to spark a renewed interest in traditional handlooms, especially among the younger generation. In an age where fast fashion dominates, seeing timeless sarees worn with pride and purpose on a mainstream platform may encourage viewers to revisit their cultural wardrobes.</p><p>This could lead to a revival of lost weaves and techniques, giving a boost to artisans who have preserved these crafts for generations.</p>",
