            "txt_align": "start",
            "sub_heading": "",
            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2><br/></h2><h2>My Final Take</h2><p><em>Chhaava</em> is not just a historical drama—it’s a <strong>love letter to India's textile heritage</strong>, especially the saree. It reminds us that the saree is more than a garment; it’s a symbol of identity, power, and timeless beauty. With its visual richness and attention to historical accuracy, the film not only educates but inspires a deep appreciation for our traditions.</p><p><em>In 2025, sarees aren't just surviving—they're stealing the spotlight. And Chhaava is leading the charge.</em></p>",
